The paper focuses on automated refactoring of spreadsheet formulae, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The approach proposed in the paper involves detecting and removing logic redundancy, which is a common task in programming languages (cs.PL). The evaluation is conducted on a real-world spreadsheet corpus, which involves data management and analysis (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the cognitive cost for users, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Overall, the paper covers multiple sub-categories of computer science, but the focus on software engineering and programming languages makes cs.SE and cs.PL the most likely categories.
